The paper deals with the problem of cooperative data exchange (CDE) among wireless clients, which involves the exchange of packets to reconstruct the entire packet set. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI), as well as distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG) since the authors propose a steepest descent algorithm to solve the problem. The paper also discusses fairness in the distribution of communication load, which is a topic in social networks (cs.SI).
